dc_title_s: General chart of the Baltic or East Sea including the gulfs of Botnia and Finland : compiled from the surveys made by order of the admiralties of Copenhagen, Stockholm & St. Petersburgh
dct_alternativeTitle_sm: General chart of the Baltic or East Sea including the gulfs of Botnia and Finland : compiled from the surveys made by order of the admiralties of Copenhagen\, Stockholm & St. Petersburgh
dc_description_s: Cartographic Details: Scale approximately 1:600,000 (E 12°--E 31°/N 66°--N 53°). Depths shown by soundings and isolines. "Published by W. Faden, Geographer to the King and to H.R.H. the Prince of Wales, Charing Cross, June 4, 1803." Includes tabular "List of positions, astronomically ascertained, used in the construction of this chart", inset of St.-Petersburg/Kronstadt region, and inset of Revel (Tallinn) region.; 1:600,000
